content: Have been lucky getting online network into Reach themselves by circulating this. https://www.instagram.com/s/aGlnaGxpZ2h0OjE4MDA3MzAzMzg4NjUxNDk2?story_media_id=3484719093830430762&igsh=MXR1dHB1NTN3OW1wbA==
<@1251571892201197608> says her phone banking went well today.  Even though that is not online, it will probably prompt some online donations and volunteer sign ups.

<@1277151707217793047> says made 2 hours of bilingual calls to Wisconsin yesterday.  Talked with some Harris voters and some leaning Harris, and helped some with voter registration info.  Also posted some Reach content on Facebook, and news with pro-Harris commentary.
<@1252681241778589787> Engaged with several misinformation and dis information posts on X. Ensured all of my family and friends have early voted or have a plan to vote via text and in person.
I helped connect someone with Grassroots OE options and to understand that they were still a valued part of the campaign.
<@734718412017762345> Content shared on Reddit and YouTube. Lots of positive engagement in comments. Today experienced far fewer MAGA trolls. Maybe they are all at MSG (Madison Sq Garden).
<@1202741647096545300> - I had a few post reach over 1M- my most recent 2.8M on various voting topics. I have also tackled much misinformation on X -

<@1277403387238940713>: Voters in NC who needed to feel confident that their votes do matter, and appreciated the calls.  Also greatly appreciated the info we provided re polling places, ride assistance, etc.  Also ensuring Houston rally attendees had all the info they needed.
Posted on X and shared my action cards for Jon Tester - MT and Colin Allred - TX.

Campaign and Grassroots Results Include:
- Create digital strategy outline, which can be used at scale; identifying wins and where opportunities might be regained
- Continuing to amplify digital messaging of the campaign and among house reps in close races in my state, and a few beyond that
- Continuing to push back on mis/disinformation via CNs, within FB groups, linking to voter resources and primary sources on Twitter, and within/across live podcasts
- Continuing to provide Just-in-Time training and resources in re: Discord, online privacy & safety, generating online engagement, and video editing
- Continuing to connect volunteers to resources, while providing a safer space to explore niches where they can be their best selves
